# Division template historical names system. Is a new method of naming the divisions based on the names-group assigned to it's template.
# If we run out of all historical names, the names will be assigned in the old way.
#
# Each group has a made up tag. Use it if you want to append more, or replace existing names with the extra txt files (modding).
#
# for_countries - lists all countries that can use it. If empty, or entire tag is missing, all countries in the world can use it.
#
# can_use - is a trigger that locks/unlocks the group under specific circumstances. The trigger is in a country scope.
#
# division_types - is a list of tokens to corresponding unit types. A player can in fact use any group of names for a div.template
#                  however this tag is a helper for an automated choice (for AI, or if the group must switch on it's own, because
#                  for example the current one is no longer available due to the can_use trigger saying so).
#                  In automated choice, the division template must have at least 1 of the following types for it to be chosen.
#
# fallback_name - Is going to be used if we run out of the scripted historical names. If you want to use the old division naming
#                 mechanics to be used for fallbacks, then just skip this option.
#
# unordered - It's a list of historical division names that did not have a number. Regardless if such names happened in history or not
#             this option is available here mainly for a mods.
#
# ordered - Is a list of all historical names. 
#           Numbers must start from 1 and up. 
#           Numbers can't repeat in one scope.
#           If you script the name for this group, at the same number (for example in a mod in another file), the name will be override.
#           All arguments between the brackets must be separated by spaces. Each argument is wrapped in "quotas".
#           1st argument = The name. It must contain either: 
#                          %d (for decimal number placement)
#                          %s (for string number placement - ROMAN numbers like XIV).
#           2nd argument is optional = A localizable text describing this historical division. The text will be visible in the tooltip
#                                      where you choose the historical division name.
#           3rd argument is optional = An URL preferably pointing to the WIKI. It's a future feature that is not currently working in
#                                      the current game version.
SOV_INF_01 = 
{
	name = "Rifle Divisions"

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date < 1935.01.01 
		NOT = { has_completed_focus = SOV_Tukhachevskys_Reformists }
		NOT = { has_completed_focus = SOV_Voroshilovs_Old_Guard }
		NOT = { has_completed_focus = SOV_STAVKA }
	} 

	division_types = { "infantry" "light_infantry" "bicycle_battalion" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

SOV_INF_45 = 
{
	name = "Rifle Divisions" # 1945.1.1

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1944.12.31
		has_start_date < 1945.12.31
	}

	name = "Motorized Divisions" # 1939.9.1

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date < 1940.01.01
		OR = {
			has_completed_focus = SOV_Tactical_Deep_Battle
			has_completed_focus = SOV_Defense_in_Depth
		}	
		NOT = { has_completed_focus = SOV_STAVKA }
		NOT = { has_tech = APC_1950 }
	} 

	division_types = { "motorized" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

SOV_MRD_39S = 
{
	name = "Motor Rifle Divisions" # 1939.9.1

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date < 1940.01.01
		has_tech = APC_1950
	} 

	division_types = { "motorized" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

	fallback_name = "%d-ya Motostrelkovaya Diviziya"

	# Names with numbers (only one number per entry). 
	# It's okay to have gaps in numbering.
	ordered =
	{

			has_completed_focus = SOV_Tactical_Deep_Battle

SOV_MOT_41 = 
{
	name = "Motorized Divisions" # 1941.6.22

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1940.12.31
		has_start_date < 1941.12.31
		NOT = { has_tech = APC_1950 }
	} 

	division_types = { "motorized" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

	fallback_name = "%d-ya Motorizovannaya Diviziya"

	# Names with numbers (only one number per entry). 
	# It's okay to have gaps in numbering.
	ordered =
	{

SOV_MRD_45 = 
{
	name = "Motor Rifle Divisions" # 1945.1.1

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1944.12.31
		has_start_date < 1945.12.31
		has_tech = APC_1950
	} 

	division_types = { "motorized" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

	fallback_name = "%d-ya Motostrelkovaya Diviziya"

	# Names with numbers (only one number per entry). 
	# It's okay to have gaps in numbering.
	ordered =
	{
		1 = { "%d-ya Motostrelkovaya Brestskaya Diviziya" }
		2 = { "%d-ya Motostrelkovaya Diviziya" }
		3 = { "%d-ya Motostrelkovaya Diviziya imeni Prezidiuma Verkhovnogo Soveta Krymskoy ASSR" }

	name = "Motor Rifle Divisions" # 1946.1.1
# Note: some of these units were disbanded prior to the end of 1945, but for all units this is their final wartime title.  Disbanded units later reformed carried their predecessor's honorifics so that is why they are included here.
	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1945.12.31
		has_tech = APC_1950

SOV_MEC_40 = 
{
	name = "Mechanized Divisions"

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1939.12.31
		has_start_date < 1940.12.31
		NOT = { has_completed_focus = SOV_STAVKA }
		has_tech = APC_1950
	} 

	division_types = { "mechanized" "heavy_mechanized" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

	fallback_name = "%d-ya Mekhanizirovannaya Diviziya"

	# Names with numbers (only one number per entry). 
	# It's okay to have gaps in numbering.
	ordered =
	{
		1 = { "%d-ya Mekhanizirovannaya Diviziya" }
		2 = { "%d-ya Belorusskaya Krasnoznamonnaya Mekhanizirovannaya Diviziya imeni M. V. Frunze" }

		has_start_date > 1943.12.31
		has_start_date < 1944.12.31
		has_tech = APC_1950
	} 
# After December 1943 unit names indicated how many times they had been decorated with the Red Banner.

SOV_MEC_46 = 
{
	name = "Mechanized Divisions"
# Note: some of these units were disbanded prior to the end of 1945, but for all units this is their final wartime title.  Disbanded units later reformed carried their predecessor's honorifics so that is why they are included here.
	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1945.12.31
		has_tech = APC_1950
	} 

	division_types = { "mechanized" "heavy_mechanized" }

SOV_MTN_43 = 
{
	name = "Mountain Rifle Divisions" # 1943.7.26

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1942.12.31
		has_start_date < 1943.12.31
	} 

	division_types = { "mountaineers" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_44 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

	fallback_name = "%d-ya Gornostrelkovaya Diviziya"

SOV_MTN_44 = 
{
	name = "Mountain Rifle Divisions" # 1944.6.20

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1943.12.31
		has_start_date < 1944.12.31
	} 
# After December 1943 unit names indicated how many times they had been decorated with the Red Banner.

	division_types = { "mountaineers" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_INF_01 SOV_INF_36 SOV_INF_39 SOV_INF_39S SOV_INF_40 SOV_INF_40S SOV_INF_41 SOV_INF_42 SOV_INF_43 SOV_INF_44 SOV_INF_45 SOV_INF_46 SOV_MOT_39 SOV_MOT_39S SOV_MRD_39 SOV_MRD_39S SOV_MOT_40 SOV_MOT_40S SOV_MRD_40 SOV_MRD_40S SOV_MOT_41 SOV_MRD_41 SOV_MOT_42 SOV_MRD_42 SOV_MOT_43 SOV_MRD_43 SOV_MOT_44 SOV_MRD_44 SOV_MOT_45 SOV_MRD_45 SOV_MOT_46 SOV_MRD_46 SOV_MEC_01 SOV_MEC_36 SOV_MEC_39 SOV_MEC_39S SOV_MEC_40 SOV_MEC_40S SOV_MEC_41 SOV_MEC_42 SOV_MEC_43 SOV_MEC_44 SOV_MEC_45 SOV_MEC_46 SOV_MTN_01 SOV_MTN_36 SOV_MTN_39 SOV_MTN_39S SOV_MTN_40 SOV_MTN_40S SOV_MTN_41 SOV_MTN_42 SOV_MTN_43 SOV_MTN_45 SOV_MTN_46 }

SOV_MTN_45 = 
{
	name = "Mountain Rifle Divisions" # 1945.1.1

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date > 1944.12.31

SOV_CAV_39S = 
{
	name = "Cavalry Divisions" # 1939.9.1

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = { 
		has_start_date < 1940.01.01
		OR = {
			has_completed_focus = SOV_Tukhachevskys_Reformists
			has_completed_focus = SOV_Voroshilovs_Old_Guard
		}	
		has_completed_focus = SOV_STAVKA
	} 

	division_types = { "cavalry" "armored_car_battalion" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_CAV_01 SOV_CAV_36 SOV_CAV_39 SOV_CAV_40 SOV_CAV_40S SOV_CAV_41 SOV_CAV_42 SOV_CAV_43 SOV_CAV_44 SOV_CAV_45 SOV_CAV_46 }

	}

SOV_MAR_01 = 
{
	name = "Marine Divisions"

	for_countries = { SOV }

	can_use = {
		has_start_date < 1944.12.31
		has_completed_focus = SOV_Gvardiya_Morskoy_Pekhoty
		has_tech = marines3
	}
# The tech requirement will make sure this list becomes available only later in the war if at all and makes sure there is only one available namelist to change to when you take the focus.
	division_types = { "marine" }

	# Number reservation system will tie to another group.
	link_numbering_with = { SOV_MAR_45 }

	fallback_name = "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty"

	# Names with numbers (only one number per entry). 
	# It's okay to have gaps in numbering.
	ordered =
	{
		1 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		2 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		3 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		4 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		5 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		6 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		7 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		8 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		9 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
		10 = { "%d-ya Diviziya Morskoy Pekhoty" }
	}
}
